@startuml 05-seq-upload
' docs/uml/05-seq-upload.puml
' Sequence diagram: File upload via presigned URL (Browser → MinIO direct upload).
' Что показывает: трёхшаговый процесс загрузки файла: presign → direct upload → confirm.
' Кому полезна: backend- и frontend-разработчикам для интеграции с MinIO/S3.

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam maxMessageSize 200
skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #333
    LifeLineBorderColor #666
    ParticipantBorderColor #333
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #E8EAF6
    ParticipantFontSize 13
    NoteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
}

participant "Browser" as Browser #E3F2FD
participant "NestJS API" as API #E8F5E9
participant "MinIO\n(S3-compatible)" as MinIO #F3E5F5
database "PostgreSQL" as DB #FFF3E0

== Step 1 — Request Presigned URL ==

Browser -> API : POST /issues/{id}/attachments\n{ filename: "report.pdf",\n  contentType: "application/pdf",\n  size: 2048576 }
activate API

API -> API : PlanGuard: checkLimit(tenantId, 'attachments')

alt plan limit exceeded
    API --> Browser : 402 { message: "Plan limit exceeded",\n  resource: "attachments", current: 100, limit: 100,\n  upgradeUrl: "https://app.localhost/billing/upgrade" }
else within limits
    API -> MinIO : generatePresignedUrl(\n  method: PUT,\n  bucket: "attachments",\n  key: "{tenantId}/{issueId}/{uuid}-report.pdf",\n  TTL: 60s,\n  contentType: "application/pdf")
    MinIO --> API : presignedUrl

    API -> DB : INSERT INTO issue_attachments\n{ issue_id, user_id, filename: "report.pdf",\n  url: "attachments/{key}",\n  size: 2048576 }
    note right of DB : status = PENDING\n(awaiting upload confirm)
    DB --> API : attachment { id }

    API --> Browser : 200 {\n  uploadUrl: presignedUrl,\n  attachmentId: uuid,\n  fileUrl: "/attachments/{key}"\n}
end

deactivate API

== Step 2 — Direct Upload (Browser → MinIO) ==

Browser -> MinIO : PUT {presignedUrl}\nContent-Type: application/pdf\nBody: <binary file data>
note right of Browser #E3F2FD
    File uploaded DIRECTLY to MinIO.
    API is not involved — no bandwidth cost.
end note
MinIO --> Browser : 200 OK

== Step 3 — Confirm Upload ==

Browser -> API : PATCH /issues/{id}/attachments/{attachmentId}/confirm
activate API

API -> DB : UPDATE issue_attachments\nSET status = 'READY'\nWHERE id = $attachmentId
DB --> API : OK

API -> API : EventEmitter.emit('issue.updated',\n{ issueId, attachmentAdded: true })

API --> Browser : 200 { attachment:\n  { id, filename, fileUrl, size } }

deactivate API

@enduml
